SIMPLE: retrenchment
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Retrenchment
<hw>Re*trench"ment</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>retrenchment</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act or process of
retrenching; <as>as, the <ex>retrenchment</ex> of words in a
writing</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>retrenchment</qex> of my expenses will convince you that
<?/ mean to replace your fortune as far as I can.</q>
<rj><qau>Walpole.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Fort.)</fld> <def>A work constructed within
another, to prolong the defense of the position when the enemy has
gained possession of the outer work; or to protect the defenders till
they can retreat or obtain terms for a capitulation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Lessening; curtailment; diminution; reduction;
abridgment.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Retrial</ent>⟦br⟧
